<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:If url points to an empty string (""), then &url[1] is a pointer one-past-the-end of the string object. The code dereferences url[1] and passes &url[1] to string.h functions (strstr, strrchr) and later to open(). Those string-handling calls would read through the pointer and therefore can access memory beyond the bounds of the url object, so Rule 21.17 is violated in this scenario.
</scenario>
